description:
Richard Wilson takes a journey into the past, following routes raved about in motoring guides of 50 years ago.

1. North Yorkshire Moors
Richard drives a classic Morris Minor Traveller from Scarborough to Whitby via the Yorkshire moors. On the way, he learns about the rise and fall of the British seaside resorts, takes a toll road through the Dalby Forest and checks out the Hole of Horecum. He finds out how the village of Goathland now lives a double life, and ends up with a carload of goths on their way to visit Whitby Abbey.
